description.p:
R1=an alkyl group of the formula C(n)H(2n+1) where n=0-20;


z=0,1;


R2=a linking group composed of an alkylene, or an aromatic alkylene, or an alkylene ether, or an alkylene ester, or an alkylene amide, or an alkylene urethane diradical.


Such linking groups have a total number of carbon from 2 to 20;


R3=--H, --OH, --OCH3, --OC2H5, --OC3H7, --OC4H9, --OOCR5 (where R5=alkyl radical of 1 to 5 carbons), --NH2, --NH--CO--R5;


and y=0,1.
